AWS Services Used (Phase 1)

Amazon VPC – Custom VPC, public and private subnets, route tables
VPC Peering – Secure connectivity between internal and external audit VPCs
Internet Gateway (IGW) – Public internet access for ALB and NAT
NAT Gateway – Outbound internet access for private subnets
Amazon EC2 – Web servers, application servers, jump/bastion host
EC2 Auto Scaling Group (ASG) – Automatic scaling and high availability
Application Load Balancer (ALB) – Traffic distribution across EC2 instances
Elastic Block Store (EBS) – Instance storage for EC2
Amazon S3 – Storage for static content, reports, and backups
AWS Lambda – Automated EC2 backup and start/stop scheduling
Amazon EventBridge (CloudWatch Events) – Scheduled triggers for Lambda
AWS Systems Manager (SSM) – Secure access to private EC2 instances
AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) – Roles and permissions
Amazon CloudFront – Secure content delivery for web assets
Amazon CloudWatch – Monitoring and logging
